Special Events
Besides user-generated arenas and rating-restricted events, various other special (official) arenas are not included in the rankings. These include warm-up arenas before titled arenas, one-time celebratory events, charity fundraisers, and privately-funded events with prize money. Special thanks go out to BitChess, sponsoring various events from 2016-2017, and FischyVischy, sponsoring prize funds for Revolutions, Apocalypses, and numerous other variant events and championships over the years.

We further highlight a few (series of) tournaments below:

  • Highest scores: A few 24h HyperBullet events have taken place on lichess, and naturally due to the low time control and long duration these have led to some of the highest scores ever recorded in a single arena. Users who scored more than 2000 points in one event include:
    • GM penguingim1 (2145) and GM Tayka (2023) in the BitChess 24h Hyperbullet arena;
    • Mr_Crabs (2209) and IM taheryoseph (2042) in the GM Andrew Tang Hyper Celebration event;
    • IM toivok3 (2311) and IM kiketf (2122) in the Opperwezen Roundabout.
    For variants such as Racing Kings and King of the Hill, the series of 24h "Revolution" events listed below contain some of the highest scores for these variants as well.
  • Anniversaries: Lichess hosted celebratory anniversary events in 2020, 2019, and 2018. YouTube celebrity agadmator hosted prize events when reaching YouTube milestones of 500k, 400k, 200k, and 100k YouTube subscribers.
  • Charity events: Some charity events hosted on Lichess include a tournament for the Black Lives Matter movement, the COVID-19 fundraisers Offerspill Relief and Marathon pour Mercy, and the Solidarity With Beirut arena for the victims in Beirut.
